## Permission

You may:

* read the content;
* share links to the original posts published on official Gelo websites;
* quote short excerpts for reference, commentary, criticism, discussion, or news purposes, provided that you clearly credit Gelo as the source and link to the original post when available.

## Restrictions

Without prior written permission from Gelo, you may not:

* republish full posts;
* copy full articles to another website, blog, repository, newsletter, social media account, book, dataset, archive, or publication;
* redistribute the Markdown files;
* mirror, scrape, or archive the content for public redistribution;
* sell, sublicense, or commercially exploit the content;
* remove or alter author names, source links, credits, or copyright notices;
* present the content as your own or as content created by another person or organization.

## Attribution for quotations

When quoting a short excerpt, attribution should include the name “Gelo” and, when available, a link to the original post.

Example:

```txt
Source: Gelo — https://blog.gelo.tv/
```

For a specific post, link directly to the original post URL.

